title: RBA Warns Of Elevated Inflation Deep Into 2026 Despite Holding Rates | 10 News
description: The Reserve Bank has left interest rates on hold today, even as it warns that inflation will continue to remain above its target range deep into next year. title: Melbourne Cup Day, New Solar Sharer Scheme, New York City Mayoral Race | 10 News+
description: Australian man Matt Kingston has spoken to 10 News+ about his fearful experience during the UK train stabbing attack which left 11 people injured. It comes amid revelations the suspected stabber may have been on a knife rampage 24 hours before he boarded the London-bound train, and was not stopped by anyone.  There is increasing pressure for Liberal Party leader Sussan Ley to follow the Nationals and ditch their net zero by 2050 target. The party room remains split, with one Ley supporter speaking out and urging the Liberals to remain committed to combatting climate change, in a bid to win back city seats.  Close to a million New Yorkers have already hit the polls on the eve of the city’s mayoral election. A record number of voters are expected to turn out to elect a new man in charge of America’s largest city. The front-runner is 34-year-old Zohran Mamdani, a democratic socialist who could become New York’s first Muslim mayor.  Skywatchers are in for a treat on Wednesday night, with the sky set to be lit up by a rare phenomenon, a full super beaver moon. Dr Matthew Shaw from Swinburne University spoke to 10 News+ about what makes this sight special, and where to get the best views.
